Summary:
This proxy supports HTTP/1.0 on output side and FSP v2 on input side.
FSP over HTTP/1.0. This proxy do not caches anything.

In detail:
Using this proxy, you can browse FSP sites by any web browser
which support gopher protocol. This proxy DO NOT tunels HTTP over
FSP.

Installation:

1. Get fsp javalib

This programs needs correctly installed (in CLASSPATH) jfsplib,
you can get it from main FSP protocol suite site:
http://fsp.sourceforge.net/javalib.html

2. Setup WWW browser's proxy
Setup Gopher proxy in web browser to port 9090 on host which is running
fsproxy.

3. Run fsp proxy daemon

Running:
Usage: java fspproxy [portnumber] [mime type table]

FSP proxy can load mime.types style file for mapping file extensions
to mime types. You can get this file from apache httpd distribution.

Example: java fspproxy 9090 /usr/local/etc/mime.types

Operation:

FSP Proxy runs on port by default 9090 and accepts fsp://* and gopher://* URLs
on input side. Most browser do not recognize fsp:// urls, so you have to type
gopher: instead of fsp:

Simply type in browser ` gopher://your.favourite.fsp.site/ ` and begin...

